Philippine Stocks: Asia Terminals, Eton Properties, MacroAsia

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-02T04:34:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/philippine-stocks-eton-properties-philippines-macroasia-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.2 percent to
4,326.76.  Asian Terminals Inc. (ATI)  , the smaller of the nation’s
two-listed port operators, climbed 1.3 percent to a record 7.85
pesos. The company said it may boost the 1.9 billion-peso
capital spending budgeted for this year by as much as half.  Eton Properties Philippines Inc. (ETON PM) advanced 2.5
percent to 3.26 pesos, the sharpest gain since April 20. The
company said net income increased 154 percent last year to 732
million pesos ($17 million).  MacroAsia Corp. (MAC)   surged 6.6 percent to 3.25 pesos,
the steepest advance since March 9. Lufthansa Technik
Philippines Inc., a provider of aircraft maintenance and repair
services that’s 49 percent owned by MacroAsia, will spend $30
million to expand its facility, according to an exchange filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  